    "giving a high probability to token \"I\" (if valid), because of the tendency of an LLM to generate answers such as \"I would say answer A\", as noted in (Wang et al., 2024b).",
    "Finally, it should be noted that, with either generation strategy, and with virtually no prompt engineering, each LLM was able to produce mostly valid answers.",
    "This indicates that it \"understood\" the task at hand.",
    "With NTP, it was materialized by the fact that the overwhelming majority of the probability mass was assigned to the valid answer tokens (typical mass was above 98%",
    "for foundational models as seen in Table S4, so that the issues raised by Wang et al. (2024b) do not seem to apply to our experiment)."
  ],
